description: First n digits after decimal point in the expansion of sqrt(n), or 0 if n is a square. Leading zeros omitted.
links: Harry J. Smith, Table of n, a(n) for n=1,...,256
example: a(1) = 0 because 1 is a square. a(5) = 23606 because sqrt(5)=2.236067978...
prog: (PARI) { default(realprecision, 500); for (n=1, 256, write("b060563.txt", n, " ", floor(frac(sqrt(n))*10^n)); ) } [From _Harry J. Smith_, Jul 07 2009]
author: Jason Earls (zevi_35711(AT)yahoo.com), Apr 11 2001
